results.name: "Long" prime Roman numerals. Smallest prime whose Roman numeral representation has n characters.
comment: Finite because of ambiguity of representation for n > 3999. This is the prime version of the sequence A036746 defined by John H. Conway.
link: Gerard Schildberger, The numbers from 1 to 3999 expressed as Roman numerals.
formula: a(n) = Min(k in A000040) such that A006968(k) = n.
example: 5=V, 2=II, 3=III, 13 = XIII, 23 = XXIII, 37 = XXXVIII, 83 = LXXXIII, 233 = CCXXXIII, 283 = CLXXXIII, 383 = CCCLXXXIII, 887 = DCCCLXXXVII, 2383 = MMCCCLXXXIII, 2887 = MMDCCCLXXXVII.
